article.headline: Northeastern 84, Georgia State 69
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Bobby Kelly scored 22 points and Bennet Davis added 21 and eight rebounds to lead a second-half surge that gave Northeastern an 84-69 win over Georgia State on Wednesday night. The Huskies (1-12, 2-3 Colonial Athletic Association) used a 25-5 run over the first 9:29 of the second half to erase a 14-point halftime deficit and snap a six-game losing streak. Matt Janning led Northeastern during the decisive second-half streak with 7 points, while Adrian Martinez added 6. Martinez finished the game with 16 points and Janning had 10. After shooting only 43 percent from the field in the first half, the Huskies shot 59 percent in the second half, outscoring the Panthers 53-24 after the break. Georgia State (5-10, 1-4 CAA) used separate runs of 11-0 and 12-0 to open up at 45-31 lead at halftime. The Panthers, who came into the game shooting 35 percent from 3-point range, made seven of eight 3-pointers in the opening half. Lance Perique led Georgia State with a game-high 23 points, while Rashad Chase had 12 points and 11 rebounds.
